ms. They are mostly sedentary, though will make some nomadic movements in response to drought and flowering of eucalypts. In the southeast of their range, they make some seasonal altitudinal movements, moving down from higher regions in during colder months. Diet Fuscous honeyeaters are mainly insectivorous, foraging actively mainly in outer and upper foliage, branches and trunks of eucalypts, and taking insects on the wing. They also feed opportunistically on nectar, including from eucalypts and mistletoes, lerp and honeydew. Conservation status The species is listed under the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species as a species of Least Concern. References", "shortSummary": "The fuscous honeyeater (Ptilotula fusca) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae. It is endemic to eastern Australia, where it inha…", "locations": ["森林"], "lat": -25.0, "lng": 133.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Ptilotula_fusca_-_Glen_Alice.jpg/960px-Ptilotula_fusca_-_Glen_Alice.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-ptilotula", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-ptilotula-fusca", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-ptilotula", "species": "taxonomy-species-ptilotula-fusca"}, "expandable": true, "x": -359.68, "y": 578.64, "z": 417.37}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-ptilotula", "name": "Ptilotula", "latinName": "Ptilotula", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Ptilotula（Ptilotula）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联6种鸟类，如Yellow-plumed honeyeater、White-plumed honeyeater、Yellow-tinted honeyeater等6种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 6, "x": 343.16, "y": 536.68, "z": -95.21}], "links": [{"key": "bird-fuscous-honeyeater-7f14c56c__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-ptilotula-fusca", "source": "bird-fuscous-honeyeater-7f14c56c", "target